</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1592,1799]" box="[199,1239,1628,1655]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1628,1655]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Distribution.</emphasis>
Western Europe and parts of central Europe. 
<collectingCountry box="[862,961,1629,1655]" name="Portugal" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: two northern provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1592,1799]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1665,1691]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Ecology.</emphasis>
This species has been collected in a brackish marsh and a park in 
<collectingCountry box="[1035,1134,1665,1691]" name="Portugal" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Portugal</collectingCountry>
. In northwestern Europe, it prefers rather dark swamps, both on loamy and sandy soils (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M. &amp; Meuffels, H. &amp; Grootaert, P." box="[824,1021,1701,1727]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="101 - 113" refId="ref35431" refString="Pollet, M., Meuffels, H. &amp; Grootaert, P. (1992) Geographical distribution and habitat selection of species of Hercostomus subgenus Gymnopternus in the Benelux (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). In: Van Goethem, J. L. &amp; Grootaert, P. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 8 th International Colloquium of the European invertebrate Survey, Brussels, 9 - 10 September 1991, pp. 101 - 113." type="book chapter" year="1992">
Pollet 
<emphasis box="[898,954,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al.</emphasis>
1992
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1592,1799]" box="[199,700,1736,1763]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1736,1763]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
2.3 (rare). Fairly common (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1592,1799]" box="[199,547,1772,1799]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
